verbose_text: Similarly, high systolic blood pressure (P < 0.001), increasing levels of triglycerides (P < 0.001), larger waist circumference (P < 0.001), decreasing levels of HDL (P < 0.002), and increasing A1C (P < 0.0001), C-reactive protein (P < 0.001), and serum insulin levels (P < 0.001) were associated with an increased prevalence of both retinal and gingival hemorrhaging.
